cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper introduces a new algorithm for few-shot learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The algorithm involves approximating probability distributions and using an external memory module to recall past observations. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Among these, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely categories, as the paper focuses on developing a new algorithm for machine learning tasks. The use of memory modules and probability distributions also suggests a potential connection to neural networks, which are commonly studied in the cs.NE sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on classification and reasoning tasks could also place it in the cs.CV and cs.CL sub-categories, which often deal with image and text classification problems.
